item.description:
&lt;p&gt;After a closer look at some new data, Apple&amp;#x27;s&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;a data-kpt="1" href="https://appleinsider.com/inside/iphone-18" title="iPhone 18"&gt;iPhone 18 Pro&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p&gt;modem situation may not be cut-and-dried. Here&amp;#x27;s what the latest leaks say is in store for cellular connectivity, the A20 chip, and possible camera improvements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src="https://photos5.appleinsider.com/gallery/68124-143594-67400-141876-iphone18procolorarray-xl-xl.jpg" alt="Four modern iPhones standing upright in a row, showing backs in black, white, light blue, and pink with dual cameras, plus one front view displaying a dark abstract wallpaper"/&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On June 25,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;em&gt;AppleInsider&lt;/em&gt;
&lt;a href="https://appleinsider.com/articles/26/06/25/iphone-18-pro-board-schematics-a20-pro-data-c2-modem-files-stolen-from-tata"&gt;exclusively revealed&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p&gt;that iPhone 18 Pro schematics and documents were among the more than 630GB of files taken from Tata in&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;a href="https://appleinsider.com/articles/26/06/23/hackers-steal-apple-and-tesla-data-from-tatas-iphone-factory"&gt;a cyberattack&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;p&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An initial analysis of the leaked documentation uncovered Apple&amp;#x27;s plans to use its proprietary C2 modem in the iPhone 18 Pro and iPhone 18 Pro Max. Additional details have since come to light, thanks to new research conducted by us and an analyst we&amp;#x27;ve worked with in the past.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;|&lt;/p&gt;

